<br />
I still haven't preordered OoW for my 3 accounts.  I don't see a reason to yet, and, infact, Druids getting a "rez" (which I think should have been a Mage Ability: "Call of the Fallen Hero") really makes me not want to buy OoW.  Druids are already a well-balanced class.  Why give them extra abilities that step on our toes even more?  (I have a druid alt that I like playing too!)
<br />

<br />
As far as our #1 issue, Improving pets, while the post here says "Improvements will come with the Omens of War expansion" I am guessing that it's only the new pets (66+) that SoE is talking about, otherwise they could have put a few more words in their statement saying "Improvements will come with the Omens of War expansion for all levels."  How difficult is it to add 3 words to a sentence?
<br />

<br />
I also do not see that the spells for levels 66-70 will obtainable in a reasonable fashion: why should I level to 70 when I won't be able to get any of the spells for months after OoW's release?  (My guild is not in Time or the EP yet, so I doubt we will be able to get our hands on any of the runes (or whatever it is for the spell turn in "quest") anytime soon.  If the spells are droppable, then they'll be in the bazaar for huge sums of plat: who has that kind of plat sitting around?<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1071902" target="_blank" class="postlink">Arch Mage Whazy Weemage</a>, Arch Convoker, Holder of the Orb, Master Brewer
