				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This response is 1) responsive communication; and 2) a statement that things will improve in less than three weeks. If these claims are true in some non-trivial way, this is a BIG improvement. 
<br />

<br />
It's easy to see why they would test anything major being done for pets in terms of OoW, and it might just be that what they have done won't work until the OoW code is in, which may include major changes for non-OoW zones. After waiting this long, it isn't a big deal to refrain from carping about OoW until <span style="font-style: italic">after </span> we see what it actually accomplishes.
<br />

<br />
The flip side is that this response is a <span style="font-weight: bold">promise </span>to make things significantly better with the OoW release. Failure to execute will make it almost impossible  to believe that SOE is making a good faith effort to address our concerns.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
